their agents first. Spymasters give one-word clues that can point to multiple words on the board. Their teammates try to guess words of the right color while avoiding those that belong to the opposing team. And everyone wants to avoid the assassin.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://cf.geekdo-images.com/itemrep/img/j3KnNONTvPaOqyY_pwhS9C9s5bk=/fit-in/246x300/pic2582929.jpg\" alt=\"Codenames Image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">2 - 8</td>\n<td align=\"right\">14</td>\n<td align=\"right\">15m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2019-10-02T16:12:20.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Party</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/46213/telestrations\">Telestrations</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Each player begins by sketching a TELESTRATIONS word dictated by the roll of a die. The old fashioned sand timer may limit the amount of time they get to execute their sketch, but it certainly doesn't limit creativity! Time's up! All players, all at the same time, pass their sketch to the next player, who must guess what's been drawn. Players then simultaneously pass their guess -- which hopefully matches the original word (or does it??) -- to the next player who must try to draw the word they see -- and so on.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://cf.geekdo-images.com/itemrep/img/G28zSLO9mMXGHjn5ZSY4vk0sd3Y=/fit-in/246x300/pic2523100.jpg\" alt=\"Telestrations Image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">4 - 8</td>\n<td align=\"right\">12</td>\n<td align=\"right\">30m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2019-10-02T15:33:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Party</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://gamewright.com/product/Trash-Pandas\">Trash Pandas</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Trash Pandas is a card game where you get to play as a racoon, trying to gather useful trash as you paw through the card deck. Start a collection of precious trash items, like day-old pizza or half-eaten candy, and gain points to be the best trash panda on the block. But wait, roll the dice to sabatoge other masked fiends to prevent them from taking your spot at the top, but make sure you don't mess with any Doggos that can mess with you back. Trash is treasure, and stash the most trash!</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://cf.geekdo-images.com/itemrep/img/_y-H3J7gUewKSFyTS4_lzkbblgo=/fit-in/246x300/pic3989423.jpg\" alt=\"Trash Pandas Image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">2 - 5</td>\n<td align=\"right\">8</td>\n<td align=\"right\">15m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2019-10-02T15:31:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"nglgzz/awesome-clean-tech","categoryHTML":"<h2>Companies</h2><h3>Energy</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.helloinspire.com/\">Inspire</a> | Philadelphia, USA | 2014</p>\n<p>Simplifying consumer adoption of clean energy by offering an array of affordable clean energy plans to homeowners that integrate with smart home technologies.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-02T12:52:16.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ayr-ton/awesome-geek-podcasts","categoryHTML":"<h2>In English</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://selfhosted.show/\">Self Hosted</a> - Discover new software and hardware to get the best out of your network, control smart devices, and secure your data on cloud services. Self-Hosted is a chat show between Chris and Alex two long-time \"self-hosters\" who share their lessons and take you on the journey of their new ones. A Linux Academy podcast showcasing free and open source technologies you can host yourself.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-02T12:46:51.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ayr-ton/awesome-geek-podcasts","categoryHTML":"<h2>In English</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://linuxforeveryone.fireside.fm/\">Linux For Everyone</a> - A show about the thrilling world of desktop Linux, open source software and the community creating it. For beginners and veterans alike! Hosted by Forbes' Jason Evangelho and friends.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-02T12:36:46.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ciconia/awesome-music","categoryHTML":"<h2>Audio Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://musicbrainz.org\">MusicBrainz</a> - Open Encyclopedia for Music information and Metadata, providing a unique ID for everything</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-02T11:03:14.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ciconia/awesome-music","categoryHTML":"<h2>Audio Tools</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://beets.io/\">Beets</a> - a powerful command-line music organizer and manipulator.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-10-02T10:59:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"0xnr/awesome-bigdata","categoryHTML":"<h2>Search engine and framework</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/facebookresearch/faiss\">Facebook Faiss</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/facebookresearch/faiss\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">17k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":17013,\"repo\":\"facebookresearch/faiss\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - is a library for efficient similarity search and clustering 